    "Denote θ t,n:= 2πtn p, we havez t = - 1 √ p p-1 n=0 ε n sin (θ t,n).Note that z t is a linear combination of independent Gaussian variables, hence still be a Gaussian with zero mean.",
    "Since Var(ε n) = σ 2 and the ε n 's are independent,Var[z t] = 1 p σ 2 p-1 n=0 sin 2 (θ t,n).Using the trigonometric identity sin2 u = 1 2 (1 -cos 2u), p-1 n=0 sin 2 (θ t,n) = p 2 - 1 2 p-1 n=0 cos(2θ t,n).The second sum is a geometric series whose value is 0 whenever t / ∈ {0, p 2 }:p-1 n=0 e i 4πtn p = 1 -e i4πt1 -e i 4πt p = 0.",
    "Hencep-1 n=0 sin 2 (θ t,n) = p 2 for each t = 1,..., m. Substituting back, Var[z t] = σ 2 p • p 2 = σ 2 2.",
